snippet.textDisplay: Representation matters! We have never had an African American female winner of The Voice in its 17 season history. Not even in the Top 2! There have been so many deserving African American female contestants including Sasha Allen, Judith Hill,  Kimberly Nichole, Koryn Hawthorne, Toia Jones, Kyla Jade, Ali Caldwell, Kennedy Holmes, Kymberli Joye, and Rose Short, to name a few (these 10 ladies should have at least made the Top 2 of their seasons, IMO). Again, none of these African American ladies made the top 2 of their seasons despite their magnificent singing, versatility, and stage presence. It is sad that African American female singers are not appreciated on this show. Why aren't these kinds of amazingly talented singers ever your preference or favorite to win?! Things that make you go hmmm. Representation matters and we deserve to have an African American female winner of The Voice!

snippet.textDisplay:
Guys, the show isn’t broken. The audience is.

It was proven once that more votes were coming from southern and Midwest regions than coastal areas for American Idol, and I imagine the same is true for the Voice. If you don’t like what you see, VOTE. Have other people vote. Encourage people to watch TV. Cable is dying, and probably more so in coastal areas that happen to be less country inclined.

This isn’t Jake’s fault or the show’s. He’s just a nice guy with a good voice that auditioned for the show and wanted to win. Nothing wrong with that and he has talent. If you’re going to be outraged at a result, vote a million times and tell others to.
